            <h3>Attendance</h3>
            <p>We hope that your daughter will be able to attend every meeting, but understand that 
                scheduling can be difficult with sports and other activities. The girls will be doing 
                activities and crafts that will earn badges and awards. If you have to miss a meeting, 
                please get with your troop leader so that your child keeps up with the others. You should 
                also check emails and the website for any special information you may have missed at the meeting.
            </p>
        </div>
        @*2nd Row / 3rd Column*@
        <div class="col-sm-4 bg-info-subtle p-3 rounded">
            <h3>Safety</h3>
            <p>Please fill out the drop-off/pick-up form at every meeting/outing. If someone other than a 
                parent/guardian will be bringing or picking up your child, please let your scout’s troop 
                leader know in advance. For your child’s safety, no child may be dropped off in the parking 
                lot, nor will they be released unless a parent is present to pick up or other arrangements have 
                been made in advance.
            </p><br />
            <p>Thank you so much for involving your girls in a wonderful organization. We will do anything we 
                can to make this an enjoyable and educational experience for your child. Girl Scouts gives all 
                girls the opportunity to discover their potential and the skills they need to thrive</p>
        </div>
